PNB Makes Offer for SP Setia at 3.90 Ringgit/Share, Edge Reports

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-09-28T04:37:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/pnb-makes-offer-for-sp-setia-at-3-90-ringgit-share-edge-reports.html
Permodalan Nasional Bhd., a
Malaysian state asset manager, made a takeover offer for
property developer  SP Setia Bhd. (SPSB)  at 3.90 ringgit per share, the
Edge reported online, citing Maybank Investment Bank Bhd.  This is a premium of 21.5 percent above the stock’s five-
day volume-weighted average price of 3.21 ringgit, according to
the report. SP Setia’s shares were suspended today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter at 
 bporter10@bloomberg.net  